Budget planning is the process of creating a financial plan that outlines how income will be allocated to cover expenses and save for the future. It involves forecasting income, expenses, and resource allocation, and helps individuals or organizations manage cash flow, prioritize spending, and align financial activities with strategic goals.  Budget plans contain the budget data for a budget cycle. You can have multiple budget plans that are used for various purposes. For example, you can use budget plans to create budget amounts for different organizational units. You can also use them to do comparisons and make informed decisions
